DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Homer

who   : The sovereign poet of the Greeks.
what  : Greatest of the virtuous pagans, honored in the noble castle of Limbo.
where : Circle I — Limbo.
why   : Born before the faith that might have saved him, through no fault of his own.
when  : In a green twilight without end.
how   : He sinned not, and is denied still — sorrow without torment.

class : Circle I · Limbo · the virtuous, without grace
